@startuml
title Consul Viewer TUI - Request and Data Flow

skinparam shadowing false

actor User
participant "ConsulTuiApp" as App
participant "Input Router" as Input
participant "TTL Cache" as Cache
participant "Job Queue" as Jobs
participant "Worker Thread" as Worker
participant "ConsulClient" as Client
participant "Consul API" as Api
participant "Result Queue" as Results
participant "Render Pipeline" as Render

User -> App: trigger section refresh / action
App -> Input: interpret key or action
Input -> Cache: lookup by job key

note right of Input
Space/F12 update bulk selection state.
Enter in Services/Nodes list can open
merged instances for selected rows.
end note

alt cache hit and TTL valid
  Cache --> Input: cached payload
  Input -> App: apply cached result
else cache miss or stale
  Input -> Jobs: enqueue background job
  Jobs -> Worker: dequeue job
  Worker -> Client: execute request
  Client -> Api: HTTP GET
  Api --> Client: payload / error
  Client --> Worker: parsed result
  Worker -> Cache: store successful payload
  Worker -> Results: publish job result
  Results -> App: poll and consume
end

App -> Render: rebuild visible state
Render -> App: rows + details + status text
App --> User: updated TUI

@enduml
